news.title: Indore: Buying dream house will cost you 20% more now
news.para: Developers said that in Indore, the average cost of building a residential and commercial property has increased from Rs 1,300 sq ft to Rs 2,500 sq ft.

news.title: Gurugram: Indiabulls Centrum Park residents protest against mobile tower installation
news.para: In June 2021, the RWA allowed the installation of a temporary cell on wheels (COW), for which it signed a letter of intent with a private company for one year, claimed residents.

news.title: Property registrations in Tamil Nadu a record Rs 12,700 crore
news.para: This is a leap with respect to revenues of 1,672 crore and 2,057 crore in 2019-20 and 2020-21. Chennai and Coimbatore zones have together contributed around 60% of the total income.

news.title: Bombay HC issue show-cause notice to realtor firm over unpaid Rs 90 lakh
news.para: The court said it is “prima facie satisfied” that Monarch & Qureishi Builders and partner-brothers Jayesh and Ketan Shah have committed breach of undertakings in consent terms and defaulted paying instalment due on March 10, 2022 to the flat purchasers.

news.title: Builders urge Maharashtra to defer metro cess levy by two years
news.para: The state government is planning to impose the 1% metro cess on property transactions from April 1. Developers are of the view that a new cess will only disrupt the ongoing recovery of the sector.

news.title: RERA implementation to improve post SC direction on examining states' rules: FPCE
news.para: ​Last month, the Supreme Court directed the Centre to examine whether the rules framed by various states under the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016 (RERA) are in conformity with the central legislation and subserve the interest of homebuyers.

news.title: Rajasthan: Prices of flats to go up by 10-15% from April 1
news.para: The revised rates will be effective from April 1. President, CREDAI-Rajasthan, Dhirendra Madan said, “As there is a steep jump in the prices of key raw materials, the prices of the units will be increased by 10-15% from April. Residents who are planning to buy a house should buy it in March to save the extra cost.”

news.title: Maharashtra: High premium hurdle to make land 'freehold'
news.para: Maharashtra Society Welfare Association chairperson Ramesh Prabhu said the notification did not help the housing societies with the government charging such high premiums. “It does not matter if they give an extension.

news.title: Assam starts unique ID system for land parcels
news.para: The Unique Land Parcel Identification Number (ULPIN), which has been termed as “adhaar for land”, was conceptualised under the Digital India Land Records Modernization Programme (DILRMP) for modern land governance.

news.title: Gurugram: Miffed, Chintels Paradiso residents hit streets, may move SC
news.para: Among the protesters were children and senior citizens. The residents pointed out that there had been no arrests although an FIR had been filed a month ago.

news.title: Rainwater harvesting a must for new buildings in Secunderabad
news.para: The SCB had passed a resolution unanimously, in its board meeting held in January this year, aiming to mitigate the acute water crisis. On an average, the SCB engineering wing receives 15 to 20 applications in a month for approval of building plans.

news.title: Goa-SEIAA asks builder to set up biogas plant in housing complex
news.para: ​​The Goa-SEIAA has asked that rooftop rainwater harvesting be set up in the complex and a part of the power requirement of the housing complex be met using solar energy.

news.title: Ramgarh cantonment board serves notices to 400 buildings
news.para: Under administrative control of the Union defence ministry, the CBR, which is responsible for the upkeep of the garrison town, has taken cognizance to a letter written by former MLA Shankar Choudhary.

news.title: DDA says over 22,000 applicants registered for special housing scheme 2021
news.para: "A total of 22,179 applicants have registered themselves for the scheme, out of which payments of 12,253 applicants have been confirmed and the final figure is being reconciled with banks," a senior official said.

news.title: Jharkhand puts drone survey under 'Swamitva Yojna' on hold amid tribal protest
news.para: The scheme, launched in April 2020, aims to create digital records of immovable properties of rural residents with the use of modern technology. Villagers, following the survey, will be provided property ownership cards.
